<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Row 6.ii: Place ?(of the cross).</p><p>Row 8.i: [?Place] of Agathops. </p><p>Row 8.ii: (Place) of Heptamenius </p><p>Row 8.iii.b: ? Kour [. . . ] </p><p>Row 9.i: Thracian (gladiator). </p><p>Row 9.ii: (Place) of Athanasius. (Place) of Eusebius. </p><p>Row 9.iii: ?Place of ?Eusebius. </p><p>Row 19.i: Reserved. </p><p>Row 19.ii: Reserved. </p><p>Row 20.i: Reserved. </p><p>Row 20.ii: Place</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>6.ii: If this text is complete, the translation must be 'place of the cross'; but it may have been intended to reserve a place for an individual whose name was never cut, accompanied by a cross (as in <xref type="inscription" n="765" href="080059">8.59</xref>.4, <xref type="inscription" n="765" href="080059">8.59</xref>.12).</p>
<p>See bibliography.</p>
</div>
